    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 3,
    "last_activity_date" : 1645321942,
    "last_edit_date" : 1645321942,
    "creation_date" : 1645320942,
    "answer_id" : 71190694,
    "question_id" : 41539209,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>I had this problem and Invalidate caches and restart (in android studio) didn't work for me. Sometimes the IDE doesn't recognize the class that is being tried to be imported.</p>\n<p>Add dependency in build.gradle(:app) in gradle:</p>\n<pre><code>dependencies {\n    implementation 'com.google.code.gson:gson:2.9.0'\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>And add the line:</p>\n<pre><code>import com.google.gson.Gson\n</code></pre>\n<p>Worked for me</p>\n"
  } ],
